						<summary>

						<p>Sōmasundarēśvara temple, south base.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman Rājēndra (I) Year 4.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp to God Mahādēvar Tirunandīśvaramuḍaiyār of Vayiramēghapuram alias Jananātapuram in Tirunallūr-nāḍu in Oymā-nāḍu in Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam by Chāran maṉṟi, a <hi rend="italic">maṉṟāḍi,</hi> residing in that village. </p>						

